## 1. Epistemic Model — Provenance on Every Object

Every data object in the system must expose its provenance. This is not optional metadata — it is the trust foundation that prevents hallucination loops, enables agent auditing, and allows future multi-agent consensus networks to weight evidence correctly.

```python
class ProvenanceTag(str, Enum):
    OBSERVED    = "observed"     # directly from human first-person input
    INFERRED    = "inferred"     # derived by memory agent from observed data
    RETRIEVED   = "retrieved"    # fetched from external source by horizon scout
    PREDICTED   = "predicted"    # mathematically extrapolated future hypothesis
    CALCULATED  = "calculated"   # objective computation (trends, statistics)
```

Every Qdrant point payload in every collection must include:
```json
"provenance": "observed|inferred|retrieved|predicted|calculated",
"provenance_chain": ["source_id_1", "source_id_2"]
```

`provenance_chain` lists the point IDs that contributed to this object's creation. Raw ingest points have an empty chain. Memory categories list their member point IDs. Predictions list the memory category IDs they were derived from. This makes every inference chain traceable and auditable.

