## 6. Phase 4 — Ingest Agent

### 6.1 File Watcher

```python
# watchdog monitors ./drop/{user_id}/ recursively
# on CREATE event for supported extension:
#   1. parse file by extension
#   2. classify domain (local model, no LLM)
#   3. derive temporal fields at write time
#   4. chunk at settings.chunk_size_tokens with overlap
#   5. embed each chunk (LiteLLM embed endpoint)
#   6. write to raw_ingest_{user_id} with provenance=observed
#   7. move to ./drop/{user_id}/processed/{filename}
#      NEVER delete. NEVER leave in place (prevents re-ingest on restart).
#      NEVER move to processed until Qdrant write confirmed.
```

### 6.2 Domain Classifier

Do not use an LLM. Use local zero-shot NLI classifier (`sentence-transformers`) or keyword/regex rules. Must be fast — runs on every ingest point.

