## 12. Hardening Requirements

### 12.1 Embed Model Consistency

Sentinel check on every collection write. HARD STOP on dimension mismatch.

Upgrade path:
1. Create `{collection}_v2` with new model
2. Re-embed all points
3. Verify point count match
4. Swap config pointer
5. Archive old collection for 30 days, then delete

### 12.2 Schema Drift Monitoring

Weekly Celery task. Output to `./logs/schema_drift.log`. Backfill migrations for unknown types with n > 10.

### 12.3 Backup

Daily Celery task:
```bash
# Qdrant snapshots → ./backups/qdrant/YYYY-MM-DD/
# Redis BGSAVE → ./backups/redis/YYYY-MM-DD/
# Retain 30 days. Delete older.
```

### 12.4 Migration System

Tracked via sentinel point in `shared_entity_registry` (id=0, payload.migrations=[...]). Numbered files. Idempotent. Never re-runs applied migrations.

### 12.5 LiteLLM Model Logging

Every LLM call records `model_used`, `prompt_tokens`, `completion_tokens`, `extraction_timestamp` in the resulting payload. Enables auditing if model quality variance emerges across load-balanced backends.

### 12.6 Dead Letter

All failures append to `./logs/failed_ingest.jsonl`:
